title: Rapids area Athletes of the Week
text:
Rapids area Athletes of the Week Mark Massoglia , Daily Tribune Media 2:40 p.m. CDT September 30, 2015 Buy Photo 
Year: Senior 
Sport: Football 
Tuttle scored two touchdowns, both from five yards out during the Papermakers' 31-26 South Central Conference loss to Mauston last Friday. He finished with 120 yards on 20 carries as Nekoosa slipped to 1-1 in the conference. Buy Photo 
(Photo: Megan McCormick/Daily Tribune Media) 
BRADY BALTUS 
Year: Senior 
Sport: Football 
Baltus scored on runs of 2 and 24 yards during the Royals' dominating 44-7 Cloverwood Conference victory over Loyal last Saturday. He finished with 102 yards on 14 carries for an average of seven yards a carry. Assumption improved to 5-1 overall an in the league and is playoff eligible. 
KAITLYN HESS 
Year: Junior 
Sport: Tennis 
Hess outlasted Merrill's Grace Huftel 6-1, 3-6, 6-3 to win her No. 1 singles match during the Raiders' 6-1 victory over the Bluejays Tuesday during Wisconsin Valley Conference action. The Raiders won all four three set matches and improved to 3-3 in conference dual meets heading into Thursday's WVC tournament. Hess is 3-1 at No. 1 against conference opponents. Buy Photo 
(Photo: Mark Massoglia/Daily Tribune MEdia) 
MARIAH MATTHEWS 
Year: Junior 
Sport: Cross Country 
Matthews won the girls 4K race in 17 minutes, 14 seconds during a dual meet with Marshfield last Thursday. The victory was the first in her cross country career. The Tigers edged the Raiders in the meet 23-32. Read or Share this story: http://wrtnews.co/1FFlzy8 TOP VIDEOS
